363
00:21:59.912 --> 00:22:03.452
And there has been the attempt to use taste and smell training,

364
00:22:04.392 --> 00:22:08.192
meaning that the repeat exposure to different tastes and smells over

365
00:22:08.312 --> 00:22:11.672
time, like twice a day for six months, to change the

366
00:22:11.732 --> 00:22:12.532
experience.

367
00:22:13.452 --> 00:22:16.392
And also adaptation of oral nutritional supplements

368
00:22:17.632 --> 00:22:21.332
seems to help some patients with specific taste distortions.

369
00:22:22.032 --> 00:22:25.492
What I want to leave you with is chemosensory dysfunction is prevalent,

370
00:22:25.632 --> 00:22:29.532
impactful, and under-treated. Even if no cure is available, we

371
00:22:29.552 --> 00:22:33.192
can validate, at least patients are not going to think they're crazy, and

372
00:22:33.232 --> 00:22:37.212
provide evidence-based symptom management that can improve quality

373
00:22:37.252 --> 00:22:38.592
of life in the short term.

374
00:22:39.672 --> 00:22:43.612
We can integrate any form of chemosensory dysfunction screening in

375
00:22:43.672 --> 00:22:47.311
