551
00:32:59.824 --> 00:33:03.544
expressing cells can give rise to type one, two, or three

552
00:33:03.664 --> 00:33:07.584
cells, and do so to maintain the constant

553
00:33:07.664 --> 00:33:11.244
ratio of taste bud cell types within each bud that we think

554
00:33:11.564 --> 00:33:14.824
are really important for maintaining the sense of taste.

555
00:33:15.804 --> 00:33:19.644
Now, the other thing that these cells do, these progenitors, is they give

556
00:33:19.724 --> 00:33:23.564
rise to all the cells on the surface of the tongue and in the taste papillae.

557
00:33:23.644 --> 00:33:27.184
These non-taste keratinocytes are rapidly

558
00:33:27.224 --> 00:33:30.864
renewed and form the bulk of the output of the progenitor cells.

559
00:33:32.004 --> 00:33:35.304
So you can see that just this little organ with

560
00:33:35.684 --> 00:33:39.624
60 or 100 cells, the cells have all these decisions to

561
00:33:39.704 --> 00:33:41.964
make, and they must be tightly regulated.

562
00:33:42.444 --> 00:33:46.153
How often to divide, how often to make a taste progeny, how

563
00:33:46.304 --> 00:33:50.044
often to make a type one cell. How are the fate decisions amongst cells and buds

564
00:33:50.064 --> 00:33:53.744
decided upon? How do you decide to become taste versus non-taste, et

565
00:33:53.844 --> 00:33:57.564
cetera? And there's more. So you can imagine then, with all those

566
00:33:57.604 --> 00:33:59.704
decisions, that it might really

567
00:34:00.724 --> 00:34:03.544
make the system prone to disruption.

568
00:34:05.064 --> 00:34:08.665
So we have spent the last, I would say, 10

569
00:34:09.324 --> 00:34:13.265
years now, really digging into how homeostasis

570
00:34:13.304 --> 00:34:15.784
